text: Worst experience I have ever had at a so called Christian store. The lady with frizzy hair  was rude think she was suspose to be manager. Need to hire someone that wants a job and send her home.

text: Some one else has bought them out and it's not really a discount

name: Ryan Patrick
text: I was not pleased with the actions of a clerk in the store. He did not display Godly wisdom or even common sense in general worked with a customer. I rated my experience as 1 star. I'm rating it higher now due to the response I received from customer service. They quickly responded to my email and did a very good job. Thank you.

name: Kimberly Christmas
text: Used to be a great place to get books. Selection is limited and more space is given to gifts, trinkets, and nicknames. Very disappointed. Never really go there since Life way is just a few doors down.

text: Great place to get bibles and Christian themed gifts.

text: They have a lot of random things like small pillows and trinkets.

name: Bob Day
text: Very friendly. Although I was a bit disappointed that they didn't have a box to place my gift, that I purchased I'm. Not a show stopper though, great selection of merchandise. We will shop there in the future.
